<title>ITALY: Italy December producer prices rose 0.5 pct.</title>
<headline>Italy December producer prices rose 0.5 pct.</headline>
<dateline>ROME 1997-02-18</dateline>
<text>
<p>National statistics office ISTAT gave the following Italian producer price data for December.</p>
<p>    PRODUCER PRICES	   Dec 96    Nov 96	 Dec 95</p>
<p>    Year/year change	  +0.5 pct  +0.6 pct     +6.5 pct</p>
<p>    Month/month change	-0.1 pct  +0.2 pct	0.0 pct</p>
<p>    Index (base 1990=100)    124.5     124.6	  123.9</p>
<p>Note: ISTAT said producer prices rose 1.7 pct in 1996 after a rise of 7.9 pct in 1995  </p>
<p>Istat gave the following general breakdown:</p>
<p>				  Mo/Mo change (%)    Yr/Yr change (%)</p>
<p>    Consumer goods		  0.0 pct		   +1.5 pct</p>
<p>    Investment goods		0.0 pct		   +2.9 pct</p>
<p>    Intermediate goods	 -  0.1 pct		   -0.4 pct</p>
<p>It gave the following sector-by-sector breakdown:</p>
<p>    Sector			    mo/mo (%)	     yr/yr (%)</p>
<p>    Energy products		 0.0 pct		   +5.4 pct</p>
<p>    Minerals and metals	  +0.1 pct		   -8.4 pct</p>
<p>    Non-metal minerals	    0.0 pct		   +0.8 pct</p>
<p>    Pharamceutical/chemicals   -0.3 pct		   -2.7 pct</p>
<p>    Metal works		     0.0 pct		   +1.8 pct</p>
<p>    Cars and parts		  0.0 pct		   +4.5 pct</p>
<p>    Food, drink and tobacco    -0.1 pct		   +0.2 pct</p>
<p>    Clothing, leather goods    -0.1 pct		   +0.4 pct</p>
<p>    Other goods		    -0.1 pct		   -1.3 pct</p>
<p>-- Rome newsroom +396 6782501</p>
</text>
